# Backend Rules

## Stack
Supabase (Postgres 15+) · Supabase Auth · subdomain-based multi-tenancy · RBAC with `module.action` permissions.

## Multi-Tenancy — NEVER skip these
- Every tenant-scoped table MUST have `company_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES companies(id) ON DELETE CASCADE`.
- Every query MUST filter by `company_id`. No exceptions.
- Create composite index `(company_id, <key_field>)` on every tenant table.
- RLS MUST be enabled on every tenant table with separate SELECT / INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE policies using `auth.uid()` joined to `user_roles`.

## RBAC
- Permission format: `module.action` (e.g. `sales.read`, `inventory.write`).
- Access check = company module enabled (`company_modules`) AND user has permission (`role_permissions` → `permissions`).
- Use `user_has_permission(p_user_id, p_company_id, p_permission_code)` RPC for single-permission checks.

## Database Design
- UUIDs for all PKs (`gen_random_uuid()`). TEXT not VARCHAR. `created_at` / `updated_at` TIMESTAMPTZ on every table.
- FK must specify `ON DELETE CASCADE` or `ON DELETE SET NULL` — never silent orphans.
- Use JSONB for flexible settings/metadata fields.
- Service role bypasses RLS (acceptable for backend jobs only).

## RPC Functions
- Prefix with domain: `get_user_permissions`, `pos_close_shift`, etc.
- Use `SECURITY DEFINER`. Return `TABLE` types for list RPCs.
- Always validate that the calling user belongs to `p_company_id` before returning data.

## Migrations
- File naming: `YYYYMMDD_short_description.sql`.
- Never modify an existing migration — create a new one.
- Include rollback statements. Document breaking changes inline.

## Hard Don'ts
- ❌ `SELECT *` in production queries
- ❌ NULL allowed on `company_id`
- ❌ Cross-company JOINs
- ❌ Hardcoded company or user IDs
- ❌ Missing RLS on any new tenant table
